</style><div class="util-bios"><div class="utilcol-a"><img src="/sites/default/files/inline-files/2026_03_03_new%20icon%20style_Utilities_0.svg" data-entity-uuid data-entity-type="file" alt width="150" height="150" loading="lazy"></div><div class="utilcol-b"><p>Our Utilities business operates rate-regulated natural gas distribution and storage infrastructure. We are committed to delivering safe, reliable, and affordable energy to our <strong>1.6 million</strong> residential, commercial, and industrial customers<sup>1</sup>. With a substantial rate base of approximately <strong>US$5.4 billion</strong>, our Utilities include Washington Gas and SEMCO Energy, serving customers across Virginia, Maryland, the District of Columbia (D.C.), and Michigan.</p></div></div><div style="border-top-color:#efefef;border-top-style:solid;margin:20px 0px 20px 0px;">&nbsp;</div><div class="util-bios"><div class="utilcol-c"><p><img src="/sites/default/files/inline-images/SEMCO%20horizontal_4C%20_0.png" data-entity-uuid="89800253-e7b9-47c8-a130-28b29be3c55a" data-entity-type="file" alt width="78%" height="78%" margin-bottom="20px" loading="lazy"></p><p><br>Headquartered in Port Huron, Michigan, <a href="https://www.semcoenergygas.com/">SEMCO</a><sup>2</sup> is a regulated public utility that delivers natural gas to approximately <strong>330,000 residential, commercial, and industrial customers</strong> in service territories in Michigan, covering portions of the southern half of the state's Lower and in the central, eastern and western parts of the state's Upper Peninsula.</p></div><div class="utilcol-c"><p><img src="/sites/default/files/inline-images/Washington%20Gas%20Logo_HZ-RGB.png" data-entity-uuid="45c8f0ea-d5f0-44f0-9699-81439a1bc114" data-entity-type="file" alt width="67%" height="67%" loading="lazy"></p><p><a href="https://www.washingtongas.com/">Washington Gas</a> is a regulated natural gas utility providing safe, reliable and affordable natural gas for more than 175 years. Today, Washington Gas serves over <strong>1.2 million customers</strong> in the District of Columbia, Maryland and Virginia with energy they rely on every day. Washington Gas was chartered by the U.S. Congress in 1848 and has been providing energy to residential, commercial and industrial customers ever since.</p></div><div class="utilcol-c"><p><img src="/sites/default/files/inline-images/Hampshire-Gas_Logo_rgb.png" data-entity-uuid="9da12d3f-f73c-48f2-8668-7cb7a6245725" data-entity-type="file" alt width="67%" height="67%" loading="lazy"></p><p>Hampshire Gas owns and operates interests in natural gas storage facilities in and around Hampshire County, West Virginia. A wholly-owned subsidiary of WGL Holdings, Hampshire Gas is regulated by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission (FERC) and provides exclusive storage services to Washington Gas, another WGL subsidiary.</p></div></div><ol class="parenthesis"><li class="li-notes">Including transportation and non-regulated business lines.</li><li class="li-notes">SEMCO Energy Gas Company is a division of SEMCO Energy, Inc.</li></ol><div style="border-top-color:#efefef;border-top-style:solid;margin:20px 0px 20px 0px;">&nbsp;</div><div class="util-bios"><div class="utilcol-a"><p><img src="/sites/default/files/inline-images/2025_09_30_new%20icon%20style_NG%20Gathering_0.svg" data-entity-uuid="aa374040-568c-4c47-ba2c-2f878202a8f1" data-entity-type="file" alt width="150" height="150" loading="lazy"></p></div><div class="utilcol-b"><h3>Storage Infrastructure</h3><p><a href="https://wgl.com/hampshiregas">Hampshire Gas</a> is a subsidiary of WGL that provides regulated interstate natural gas storage services to Washington Gas under a FERC approved interstate storage service tariff.</p></div></div><div class="util-bios"><div class="utilcol-a"><p><img src="/sites/default/files/inline-images/2025_09_30_new%20icon%20style_Retail%20energy_0.svg" data-entity-uuid="9a683b17-4afa-475e-a287-e8e820c1cb1d" data-entity-type="file" alt width="150" height="150" loading="lazy"></p></div><div class="utilcol-b"><h3>Retail Energy Marketing</h3><p><a href="https://www.wglenergy.com/">WGL Energy Services</a> is a subsidiary of Washington Gas Resources that sells natural gas and electricity to retail customers on an unregulated basis in Maryland, Virginia, Delaware, Pennsylvania, Ohio, D.C. and New Jersey.</p></div></div><div style="border-top-color:#ffffff;border-top-style:solid;margin:20px 0px 20px 0px;">&nbsp;</div></div>
      
